canonical:
  title: 草堂
  author: 吳洵
  language: lzh
  text: 緣樹交加黃鳥飛草堂高臥日遅遅從今漸覺風情减春盡都無一首詩
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 草堂
  author: 吳洵
  language: lzh
  text: 緣樹交加黃鳥飛。草堂高臥日遅遅。從今漸覺風情减。春盡都無一首詩。
korean:
  title: 초당
  author: 오순
  language: kor
  text: |-
    푸른 나무 얽히었고 꾀꼬리는 나는데
    초당에 높이 누워 봄날이 더디어라
    지금부터 차츰 깨닫노니 풍정이 줄어들어
    봄이 다하도록 아예 시 한 수도 없었네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0460&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 緣 : '
    value: 綠
english:
  title: The Grass Hall
  author: Wu Sun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Among verdant trees entwined, the oriole takes flight.
    In the grass hall, I lie in repose as the spring day lingers.
    Gradually now I perceive it—the season's tender charm fades.
    As spring departs, not a single poem has escaped my brush.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The grass hall (초당/草堂) likely refers to a humble thatched retreat, a common setting in East Asian poetry for contemplation and artistic endeavor.
